President Obama has called for a moment of silence to honor the victims of a shooting in Tucson, Arizona. The moment of silence will take place at 11:00 a.m. eastern standard time and Americans are encouraged to participate in prayer or reflection. The President will observe the moment of silence with White House staff on the South Lawn, and it will be pooled press. Additionally, the President has signed a proclamation calling for flags to be flown at half-staff. His planned trip to Schenectady, New York, on January 11 has been postponed and will be rescheduled.